<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>What is the best free AI detector?</strong></p>
<p>GPTZero and ZeroGPT are the most popular free options with reasonable accuracy. Hugging Face offers the most transparency for technical users. The best choice depends on your needs: simplicity, high limits, or technical control.</p>
<p><strong>Are free AI detectors accurate?</strong></p>
<p>Free detectors are generally less accurate than paid versions. All detectors have significant false positive and false negative rates. Use them as signals, not definitive verdicts.</p>
<p><strong>Can free detectors identify GPT-4 content?</strong></p>
<p>Most free detectors were trained on GPT-3 output and struggle with GPT-4. Newer models produce more human-like text that is harder to detect.</p>
<p><strong>How many words can I check for free?</strong></p>
<p>Limits vary by tool: Writer.com allows 1,500 words, GPTZero allows 5,000 characters, ZeroGPT allows 15,000 characters, and Hugging Face has no limit.</p>
<p><strong>Do free AI detectors store my text?</strong></p>
<p>Policies vary. Some tools may store text for model training. If you are checking sensitive content, read the privacy policy or use an open-source tool like Hugging Face where you control the data.</p>
<p><strong>Should I use multiple detectors?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Running text through 2-3 detectors gives you a better signal than relying on one. If multiple tools agree, the result is more meaningful.</p>
